beer.beer_name: Hit Me Up Thiolised DIPA With Phantasm
beer.beer_description:
Hit Me Up is a new DIPA with a new ingredient we've been loving of late - Phantasm - made from NZ Sav Blanc grape skins that are rich in thiol precursors. Mash hopped with NZ cascade on a base of oats, wheat, and spelt we’ve gone and then Double Dry Hopped with fresh Freestyle Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, and Citra with a post fermentation double-dose of Nelson Sauvin SubZero Hop Kief™.

If you’re looking for a vinous and citrus forward tropical juice bomb with a restrained bitterness and soft finish then Hit Me Up.

items.badge_description: It's New Brew Thursday! Drink any beer you have never had before on three different Thursdays in a 20 day period.

When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 160 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 33!
